description*.en: Angular acceleration is the rate of change of angular velocity over time. Measurement of the change made in the rate of change of an angle that a spinning object undergoes per unit time. It is a vector quantity.  Also called Rotational acceleration. In SI units, it is measured in radians per second squared ($rad/s^2$), and is usually denoted by the Greek letter alpha.
